The Federation of Public Service Game (FEPSGA) is making adequate preparations to resume it’s monthly keep fit walking and jogging exercise. The monthly exercise has not taken place for almost a year following the outbreak of Coronavirus which affected sporting activities across the world. Speaking the President of the Federation, Aloku Amaebi said; “the  Federation is working assiduously in making sure that the monthly keep fit exercise resumes as every  modalities of the COVID -19 will be strictly adhered to. “Workers must continue to engage in their regular physical exercise to remain productive.” Meanwhile, the Federation has appreciated the Governor of Kano State, Abdullahi Ganduje for hosting the 39th edition of the Federation of Public Service Game in Kano December, 2020. This year’s edition which is the 40th will come up in December in a yet to be named State. 